column39: MPAs advocated to protect large (> 140 mm carapace length) rock lobsters against overharvesting by the commercial fishery on Tasmania's east coast. These lobsters predate upon C. rodgersii and MPAs and the return of strong lobster predation within them would appear to confer maximum resilience of kelp beds against C. rodgersii overgrazing and subsequent formation of urchin 'barrens'. These urchins threaten the productivity of the Tasmanian abalone fishery, the world's largest, supplying ~25% of the global wild capture market, as well as the rock lobster and scalefish fisheries, through loss of productive reef habitat.
